<div id="pf4ff5" class="pf w47 h356" data-page-no="4ff5"><div class="pc pc4ff5 w47 h356"><div class="t mae7 x63 h1 y3052 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t ma71 x3f h1 y3036 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did Moses similarly address God? Psalm 90:2. &apos; </div><div class="t m308 x5b h1 y2bc0 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t mf36 x3f h1 y2bc0 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Summarize how the psalmist speaks of God as Judge in Psalm 50:1-6. </div><div class="t m486 x5b h1 y2878 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t md1a x3f h1 y294e ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did Moses describe God to the children of Israel? Deut. 4:24. </div><div class="t m486 x5b h1 y27e ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t ma63 x3f h1 y917 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What does fire issuing from God do? Psalm 97:3. </div><div class="t m315 x4e h1 yaa ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ILLUMINATION: </div><div class="t m68f x6a he y15c7 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Daniel is shown the final judgment in both its phases, in-</div><div class="t md14 x60 he ya38 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">vestigative and executive. . . . The investigation is not conducted for the infor-</div><div class="t m79a x4e he y281 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">mation of God or of Christ, but for the information of the universe at large—that </div><div class="t m40e x4e he y3ee ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God may be vindicated in accepting some and rejecting others.&quot;—SDA </div><div class="t mf32 x195 h21 y6e8 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bible </div><div class="t m7fe x4e h21 ya25 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Commentary, </div><div class="t m481 x40 he ya25 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">vol. 4, p. 828. </div><div class="t m7db x5b h21 y5c2 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The judgment was set.&quot; </div><div class="t mb57 x99 he y4ff ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The words are simple, but the implications are tre-</div><div class="t m362 x4e he y1d1 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">mendous! The fate of every individual will be decided forever. </div><div class="t m3d4 x5b h21 y48a ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The books were opened.&quot; </div><div class="t m344 x7d he y48a ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Bible refers to a number of &quot;books&quot; of </div><div class="t m7e3 x4e he y402 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">records. </div><div class="t m45f x4e h1 y8e2 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SEARCH AND LEARN: Read the following texts and list the names of the </div><div class="t m1154 x4e h1 y9 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">books indicated: </div><div class="t m111e x63 he yd33 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ps. 69:28 </div><div class="t m5 xb he y91 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1384 x1db he y91 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m91b x63 he y9e6 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mal. 3:16 </div><div class="t m5 xb he y9e6 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1384 x1db he y9e6 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m9b5 x63 he y91b ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Phil 4</div><div class="t m1058 xf he y5fe ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">.</div><div class="t m13aa x10 he y5fe ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3 </div><div class="t m5 x1 he y5fe ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1384 x1db he y5fe ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m33c x63 he y658 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Rev 3</div><div class="t m1058 xd he y657 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">.</div><div class="t m28a xf he y657 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5 </div><div class="t m5 x19 he y657 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1384 x1db he y657 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t mf31 x63 he y9d3 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Rev. 20:12 </div><div class="t m5 xcf he y9d3 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1384 x1db he y9d3 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t mcf x63 he y2c4 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The records are kept so that anyone in the universe who might challenge God&apos;s </div><div class="t m5dc x4e he y306 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">justice can have access to the facts involved. </div><div class="t m2f9 x63 h1 y5db ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What is one outcome of the judgment? Dan. 7:11. </div><div class="t m320 x63 he y1ab ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">As a result of the judgment the persecuting beast and the blasphemous horn </div><div class="t m93 x4e he y851 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">will be destroyed. God is the source of life, but the wages of sin and rebellion is </div><div class="t me55 x4e he ydee ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">death. Note how thorough the destruction will be: (I) The beast is slain, and the </div><div class="t m1c9 x4e he y83 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">horn with it—it can no longer be active, (2) the body is destroyed—there is no </div><div class="t m567 x4e he yc73 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">possibility of its reappearance, and (3) the body is given to the burning flame—</div><div class="t me55 x4e he yb67 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">there is no possibility of contamination. </div><div class="t m1196 x4e h1 y3b7 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">58 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
